HEADWORD: Charlatan
<hw>Char"la*tan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>charlatan</ets>, fr. It. <ets>ciarlatano</ets>, fr.
<ets>ciarlare</ets> to chartter, prate; of imitative origin; cf. It.
<ets>zirlare</ets> to whistle like a thrush.]</ety> <def>One who prates
much in his own favor, and makes unwarrantable pretensions; a quack; an
impostor; an empiric; a mountebank.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

